<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
            <title>LO RANGE GEAR AND OUTPUT SHAFT</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Stand the output shaft on end with the rear of the shaft facing up. Place auxiliary
                    housing over the shaft so that the output shaft extends through the rear bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029h8">Figure 178</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13029h8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13029h8" filename="../figg13/G13029H8.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 178. Place Auxiliary Housing Over Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a heat lamp or hot plate and oil to heat the output shaft rear bearing and install
                    it on the output shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029h9">Figure 179</hotlnk>). Seat the bearing securely on the shaft and in the
                    bore. Bearing can also be installed using the appropriate driver.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13029h9" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13029h9" filename="../figg13/G13029H9.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 179. Heat Output Shaft Rear Bearing and Install on Output Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not heat the bearing above 275&#176;F (136&#176;C).</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
